subs.text: I have the Apple credit card. It's so incredibly easy to pay the bill, because the UI is right there on your iPhone. I also now have an Amazon card, and two traditional bank cards. So I know from what I'm talking about.
We had an explosion of rabbits this summer, but then I realized I haven't seen one rabbit in many weeks. Where did they go? Do rabbits hibernate? Migrate?

It's not often you know that next Tuesday the world is going to change in a profound way. There's still a chance the world will fall apart before then, as a programmer I am trained to think of all that can go wrong. But barring that, one way or the other everything will change a week from today.
